  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.1417" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <opener>My dear Prof. Schuchardt,</opener>
        <p>Your card of Sep. 25<hi rendition="#sup">th</hi> was duly received. Mr. <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.3337">Benjamin Sulte</persName>
          <note n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.3337">Benjamin Sulte</persName> (1841-1923) war ein kanadischer Journalist, Schriftsteller und Historiker.</note> is an employee in one of the Canadian Goverment [sic] Bureaus, at Ottawa. He knows nothing about language, except as a general historian. He is considered one of the best young historians in Canada and is a great producer in that Department. His article<note
            n="2" place="foot"
                type="editorial">Gemeint ist vermutlich der folgende Artikel Sultes: <bibl>

Sulte, Benjamin. 1877. ‘Notre Langue‘. In <hi
                rend="unknown"
            rendition="#none">
Revue de Montréal</hi> I:657-668
</bibl>.</note>, to which you refer, is wholly unscientific and superficial. I have just begun to publish the preliminary parts of my work on Canada,<note
            n="3" place="foot"
                type="editorial">
Gemeint wird vielleicht der folgende Artikel: <bibl>


Elliott, A[aron] M[arshall]. 1885. ‘Contributions to a History of the French Language of Canada‘. In <hi
                rend="unknown" rendition="#none">American Journal of Philology</hi> VI, 2: 135-150.
</bibl>

          </note> which I shall send you as soon as they appear. I have spent a part of my summer in the maritime provinces (Cape Breton, Isle Madame &amp; Nova Scotia) of Canada, and have collected a large amount of supplementary material on the French Acadian languages, which I propose to use in my work. <pb
            facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/> I was in Germany in July and expected fully to see you, but was detained at Ems<note
            n="4" place="foot" type="editorial">Gemeint wird <placeName>
Bad Ems</placeName>.</note> longer than I had thought to be when I left home. I hope next summer to be able to see you somewhere over there.</p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Hoping you are very well, I am, as ever,</salute>
          <lb/>
          <salute>Yours very sincerely,</salute>
          <lb/>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1447">A. M. Elliott</persName>
          </signed>
        </closer>
      </div>
    </body>
